# e2e-homeric-compose-cpp-pipeline — History

## v1.6.0 (2026-04-21)

**Changed by:** Docker Compose v5 healthcheck array-splitting regression, BusyBox wget flag fix, Prometheus IP patch for podman run --replace services, idempotency guards, teardown orphan cleanup. Full E2E pass on Docker Compose v5.0.2 + podman 4.9.3, WSL2. PR #117.
**Verification:** verified-local (Odysseus PR #117, Docker Compose v5.0.2 + podman 4.9.3, WSL2)

### What changed
- Added Failed Attempt: `["CMD","sh","-c","full cmd"]` JSON array healthcheck splits 4th element on spaces in Docker Compose v5 — wget runs without `-c` argument
- Added Failed Attempt: `["CMD-SHELL","full cmd"]` array form also splits on spaces in Docker Compose v5 — confirmed via `podman inspect`
- Added Failed Attempt: `wget -qO-` combined flag rejected by BusyBox wget in nats:alpine — use `-q -O /dev/stdout` instead
- Added Failed Attempt: Prometheus scraping argus-exporter by hostname fails when argus-exporter is started via `podman run --replace` (not compose-managed DNS)
- Added Failed Attempt: `podman cp` to overwrite read-only bind-mounted Prometheus config fails with "device or resource busy"
- Added Failed Attempt: `just e2e-test` calling `start-stack.sh` while stack already up causes compose name conflicts from `podman run --replace` containers
- Added `healthcheck_string_form` Results block: YAML string (no array) works on both Docker Compose v2 and v5
- Added `busybox_wget_healthcheck` Results block: BusyBox-compatible wget flags for nats:alpine
- Added `prometheus_ip_patch` Results block: resolve argus-exporter IP and hot-reload Prometheus after podman run --replace
- Added `idempotency_guard` Results block: curl health-check guard at top of start-stack.sh and run-hello-world.sh Phase 1
- Added `teardown_orphan_cleanup` Results block: explicit podman rm for containers started outside compose
- Updated description frontmatter to note YAML string healthcheck requirement for Docker Compose v5
- Bumped version 1.5.0 → 1.6.0, updated date to 2026-04-21
- Added Odysseus PR #117 Docker Compose v5.0.2 / podman 4.9.3 / WSL2 row to Verified On table

### Why
Docker Compose v5 (snap package, v5.0.2) introduced a regression where healthcheck `test:` arrays are tokenized on spaces before passing to the container runtime — the 4th element of `["CMD","sh","-c","wget ..."]` is split, so `sh -c wget` receives no command string. The fix is to use plain YAML string form (`test: "cmd"`), which both v2 and v5 treat as CMD-SHELL without splitting. Additional failures surfaced around BusyBox wget flag differences in nats:alpine and Prometheus DNS resolution for containers managed outside compose.

