## v1.5.0 (2026-04-06)

**Changed by:** Three new failure modes from 2026-04-06 Odysseus E2E walkthrough
**Verification:** verified-local (fixes committed to Odysseus main 2026-04-06)

### What changed
- Added Failed Attempt: `task.created` event silently dropped by Hermes (only `task.updated`, `task.completed`, `task.failed`, `agent.*` supported)
- Added Failed Attempt: `worker.py` nonexistent in hello-world myrmidon (correct file: `main.py`, subscribes to `hi.myrmidon.hello.>` via JetStream push consumer)
- Added Failed Attempt: CMD-SHELL array format rejected by podman-compose 1.5.0 (use `["CMD", "sh", "-c", "..."]` for dual-runtime compatibility)
- Updated `hermes_event_types` Results block with explicit valid event type list and zero-error silent-drop callout
- Added `hello_world_myrmidon_worker` Results block documenting `main.py` entrypoint and NATS subjects
- Added `healthcheck_cmd_array` Results block with dual-runtime compatible healthcheck template
- Updated description frontmatter to add items (6) and (7) covering Hermes event mapping and CMD array format

### Why
The 2026-04-06 full E2E walkthrough on epimetheus uncovered three new failure modes not present in prior sessions. The Hermes webhook event type bug caused Phase 3 of run-hello-world.sh to silently succeed (webhook accepted) but publish nothing to NATS. The worker.py issue caused start-myrmidon to fail with "No such file or directory". The CMD-SHELL format caused podman-compose 1.5.0 to reject all healthcheck definitions.

